Making a sponge cake is very easy, you only need eggs, sugar, and flour as the main ingredients. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Preheat your oven to 180Â°C, then grease down your baking tin. Step 2 Using a medium-sized bowl and whisk, mix the butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Step 3 Break the eggs into a bowl and beat lightly, then add milk. Combine then add little by little the butter/sugar mix, beating well after each addition. Step 4 Add the flour little by little to the egg and butter mix, folding gently then add the lemon rind and combine. Step 5 Pour the mixture into the baking and bake for 45 to 50 minutes until firm to the touch or until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean. Step 6 Remove from the oven and let it cool for a couple of minutes, then put it on the rack to cool. Grate the remaining lemon zest and enjoy. Serve with a preferred beverage or cold milk.